<item>
            <title>[HBASE-10330] TableInputFormat/TableRecordReaderImpl leaks HTable</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-10330</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As far as I can tell, TableInputFormat creates an instance of HTable which is used by TableRecordReaderImpl. However TableRecordReaderImpl.close() only closes the scanner, not the table. In turn the HTable&apos;s HConnection&apos;s reference count is never decreased which leads to leaking HConnections.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;TableOutputFormat might have a similar bug.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
